<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-12-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-12-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="1627" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1627">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.73/3.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-12-19">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 19, 1911</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to the Department’s instruction
                            No. 14, of the 15th instant, and to the Department’s telegram of
                            December 16, the Department <pb facs="1324" n="1208" xml:id="pg_1208"/>
                            encloses herewith for your information and for appropriate action a copy
                            of a letter dated December 13, 1911, from the Acting Secretary of the
                            Navy in which is quoted the following recommendation of the Joint Board
                            of the Army and the Navy, dated November 27, 1911, and approved by the
                            President under date of December 12, 1911: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>2. That an understanding be reached with Panama to prevent the
                                    establishments of private and commercial wireless installations
                                    in its territory.</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <p>A copy of an unnumbered despatch,<note n="1" xml:id="d1627fn1">Not
                                printed.</note> dated November 29, 1911, from the American Consulate
                            General at Panama on the same general subject is also enclosed
                            herewith.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>(For <signed>Mr. Knox</signed>:) <lb/>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>